node.text:
Here is our third and final part of our discussion with Hera from @ChaynHQ and Romina from @EqualityNowOrg !!

Through a tech and legal lens, Hera and Romina answer questions about exploitation submitted by you! Thank you all who submitted questions, and thank you to everyone who has been watching these past few days. @vanessamarano and I are also so grateful to Hera and Romina for taking time out of their schedules to have this conversation with us. As always, our goal is to have an informative and open discussion about this issue and find out ways in which we can combat it. 

Thanks again so much for watching and learning with us, and please share to anyone you think would be interested in learning more about this issue.

Find out more about @ChaynHQ by going to
https://chayn.co/

Find out more about @EqualityNowOrg at
https://www.equalitynow.org/

Resources regarding exploitation:

The National Human Trafficking Hotline
https://humantraffickinghotline.org/report-trafficking

RAINN
https://www.rainn.org/

National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC)
https://www.missingkids.org/gethelpnow
https://www.missingkids.org/gethelpnow/isyourexplicitcontentoutthere

StopSextortion
https://www.stopsextortion.com/

node.text:
Vanessa and I pick up right where we left off yesterday with Romina from @equalitynoworg and Hera from @ChaynHQ. We discuss how exactly victims of online sexual exploitation are protected, if websites who facilitate trafficking are held accountable, and more!

One important topic we talk about is what lens policymakers should be using when making laws or policies about the internet. There are plenty of beautiful and positive aspects of the internet and technology we use, so how do we keep those aspects while also bringing light to the darker corners of the web (Hera has a wonderful metaphor about this exact point)? 

Thank you so much for watching!

node.text: It’s the last Monday of 2020 😩🙌 this last week of the insane year we call 2020, I wanted to spend it with you...and YOU, soooo I’m going to be posting some videos from my YOU Tour, doing some listening parties, and crashing some Zooms. Thank you to everyone who’s been streaming and loving the music I put out this year...it’s truly permanently made me this face 🥺 To start us off, I’d thought I’d post this YOU themed medley I did during my first show. Ironically, it has no songs from the You EP, buuut it’s some of my favorite You themed songs, and I had a lot of fun covering them...enjoy! Also, be sure to listen to my EP all weeeek with the link in my bio 🤓

node.title: YOU Themed Medley featuring “Into You,” “Love on Top,” and More!

node.text:
Self timer strikes again 👽
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨
Tomorrow is the first show of six shows that I’m doing for the next month and a half!!!! Every Sunday for the next six weeks, I’ll be playing a stripped down version of one of the songs from my You EP, and then doing a Q&A with fifteen of my fans about the themes of the song (plus some other surprises)😊You can get a ticket to watch the show, aaaand you can get a ticket to actually be part of the show and in the Q&A! Go to the link in my bio to get your tickets 🙌🙌🙌 More info can be found in the Sundays w/ Me highlight on my profile ❤️
